<p class="">Is it not a fact in works of a similar kind in South Wales that while the labour employed has been drawn from local Employment Exchanges, people outside have oftentimes <span id="227" class="column-number" data-column-number="227"></span> been brought m, registered at the local exchange and then employed on the works, excluding local labour?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
